Both output files are written. Summary of what was found:

**Headline finding:** A near-pure five-way biomarker interaction dominates the response signal.

- **Triple AND-interaction** of `feature_001`, `feature_014`, `feature_021` (each ~30–40% prevalent, statistically independent in the cohort): only the triple-positive cell (n=2,401) shows elevated ORR (63.3%); all 7 other cells are at 15.7–17.2% baseline. The 3-way logistic interaction term β=+2.13 (p=4e-92), while all main and pairwise terms are essentially null.
- **Two pure interactive suppressors**, `feature_026` and `feature_009`: each has only a tiny marginal association (-2.3 pp, -2.4 pp) but acts as a near-complete antagonist within the triple-positive subgroup (β≈-2.7, p<1e-50). Outside the triple, neither feature has any effect.
- **5-feature subgroup** `(feature_001=1, feature_014=1, feature_021=1, feature_026=0, feature_009=0)`: n=1,790, ORR=78.6% vs 16.5% (OR=18.6).
- **6-feature hyper-responder** adding `feature_004=0`: n=617, ORR=85.9% (OR=27.9).
- `feature_004` is an independent ordinal prognostic (23%/17%/13% across levels 0/1/2) that further stratifies the high-response subgroup but does not interact on the log-odds scale.
- An exhaustive screen ruled out any other binary 3-way subgroup with ORR > 0.40, and 15 other continuous features (including `feature_011`, likely age) have no triple-modifying effect.

Files written: `transcript.json` (14 iterations, 23 hypotheses, 23 analyses; schema-validated) and `analysis_summary.txt`.
